SCENE: INT. RESTAURANT - NIGHT

22
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:56,610
CHARACTERS: BAMBI &amp; PRIM

23
00:00:56,680 --> 00:00:58,850
BAMBI WAITS FOR PRIM
TO CELEBRATE HER BRTHDAY TOGETHER.

24
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:00,770
PRIM CAN’T COME. SHE IS TIED UP WITH WORK.

25
00:01:06,450 --> 00:01:07,250
Hello, Prim.

26
00:01:07,530 --> 00:01:08,860
I’m going to be a bit late.

27
00:01:08,890 --> 00:01:10,500
The filming is wrapping up late.

28
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:12,200
I’ll go there as soon as I finish.

29
00:01:14,289 --> 00:01:16,300
You know today is my birthday.

30
00:01:16,850 --> 00:01:18,500
Why did you take the job?

31
00:01:18,760 --> 00:01:21,000
This is my last year in college.

32
00:01:21,030 --> 00:01:22,250
I got a chance to work
as a director's assistant.

33
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:24,300
I can’t pass on the opportunity.

34
00:01:24,920 --> 00:01:26,800
You know I work really hard.

35
00:01:28,730 --> 00:01:30,900
Bambi, I’m sorry.

36
00:01:31,140 --> 00:01:32,500
You are not mad at me, right?

37
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:35,200
No.

38
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:37,450
I’m not mad at you.

39
00:01:38,520 --> 00:01:40,300
I like seeing you happy.

40
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:42,100
(You should go back to work.)

41
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:44,300
Focus on the work and hurry to see me.

42
00:01:44,450 --> 00:01:46,300
Okay, I’ll hurry to see you. Bye.

43
00:01:47,910 --> 00:01:48,940
Prim, are you ready?

44
00:01:48,970 --> 00:01:49,979
Yes. I’m coming.

45
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:22,200
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

46
00:02:23,180 --> 00:02:24,900
Happy birthday, my girlfriend.

47
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:26,500
Make a wish.

48
00:02:38,490 --> 00:02:39,500
Let’s break up.

49
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:42,200
Bambi.

50
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:48,700
Why did you say that?

51
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:52,640
I told you this work is important to me.

52
00:02:52,690 --> 00:02:55,300
I know how much this work means to you.

53
00:02:56,780 --> 00:02:57,750
What about me?

54
00:03:03,470 --> 00:03:05,320
Do I mean anything to you?

55
00:03:08,570 --> 00:03:10,380
I want to be your priority.

56
00:03:10,410 --> 00:03:12,250
I want to be the first one that you think of.

57
00:03:12,700 --> 00:03:16,400
I don’t get why I have these questions
when I’m your girlfriend.

58
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:21,190
I’m sorry.

59
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:23,500
It won’t happen again.

60
00:03:25,970 --> 00:03:27,800
It’s okay, Prim. I get it.

61
00:03:28,970 --> 00:03:30,490
It will happen again.

62
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:34,200
I’m trying. Don’t you see?

63
00:03:34,420 --> 00:03:35,200
Yes.

64
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:37,500
But it’s not enough for me.

65
00:03:40,850 --> 00:03:42,329
I’m self-centered.

66
00:03:44,100 --> 00:03:47,600
When I’m in a relationship,
I want to be her priority.

67
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:50,480
I can’t ask you to leave everything
to do what I want.

68
00:03:50,510 --> 00:03:52,800
I think it’s never going to work
between us.

69
00:03:53,230 --> 00:03:53,900
No.

70
00:03:54,690 --> 00:03:55,400
No.

71
00:03:56,350 --> 00:03:57,600
Calm down.

72
00:03:58,240 --> 00:03:59,600
I think I can do it.

73
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:02,400
I can handle work and take care of you.

74
00:04:03,310 --> 00:04:04,500
You can stop trying.

75
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:09,300
I don’t want to be your burden anymore.

76
00:04:26,090 --> 00:04:28,430
My birthday wish this year.

77
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:33,500
I wish you success in everything
you’ve been working for.

78
00:04:36,650 --> 00:04:39,800
One day, when we are both ready,
we can get back together.

79
00:04:41,490 --> 00:04:43,400
But I think
we should be just friends for now.

80
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:50,450
SCENE: INT. BLOSSOM - NIGHT

81
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:52,290
CHARACTERS: PRIM &amp; BAMBI

82
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:54,370
PRIM AND BAMBI GET BACK TOGETHER
AND THEY ARE VERY MUCH IN LOVE.

83
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:31,350
Min.

84
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:32,450
Look.

85
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:34,100
That couple.

86
00:06:34,980 --> 00:06:36,300
I set them up.

87
00:06:38,330 --> 00:06:38,900
Ant.

88
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:40,400
Can I have a cocktail?

89
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:41,900
Sure. What do you want to order?

90
00:06:41,980 --> 00:06:43,360
Sex on Fire.

91
00:06:44,060 --> 00:06:45,000
What do you want to drink?

92
00:06:46,630 --> 00:06:47,580
Kiss Me More.

93
00:06:47,630 --> 00:06:49,500
You’re talking about the cocktail, right?

94
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:51,800
Sure.

95
00:06:52,460 --> 00:06:53,550
I’ll go to the bathroom.

96
00:06:56,810 --> 00:07:00,200
Are you here to get some air?

97
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,800
You two were kissing for so long.

98
00:07:02,490 --> 00:07:03,550
Stop teasing me.

99
00:07:03,860 --> 00:07:05,900
It’s not wrong to reignite the spark.

100
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:06,900
Ant.

101
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:09,100
Do you sell dog food as a snack?

102
00:07:09,340 --> 00:07:11,100
I’m going to eat it as a drinking snack.

103
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,690
Ant, help me.

104
00:07:13,460 --> 00:07:15,500
Stop nagging her.

105
00:07:15,540 --> 00:07:16,900
Look at my girlfriend and me.

106
00:07:17,340 --> 00:07:18,900
We’ve been on and off several times.

107
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:19,980
Look at us now.

108
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:21,000
How are you two doing?

109
00:07:21,270 --> 00:07:22,620
We are getting married.

110
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:24,100
See? Look.

111
00:07:24,260 --> 00:07:29,500
Sometimes, you need to spend time apart
to know how you really feel.

112
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,960
Maybe this time,
it will last until death parts you.

113
00:07:34,070 --> 00:07:37,100
Thank you for taking my side.
But to no need to mention death.

114
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:39,400
I’ll go to the bathroom.

115
00:07:39,610 --> 00:07:40,860
You, a straight switches teams.

116
00:07:40,890 --> 00:07:42,300
I may switch teams,

117
00:07:42,850 --> 00:07:44,810
but I surely won’t go back to my ex.

118
00:07:45,530 --> 00:07:47,080
You two.

119
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:48,400
Min.

120
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:50,550
You are her friend.

121
00:07:50,770 --> 00:07:52,470
If she refuses to listen to you,

122
00:07:52,650 --> 00:07:54,600
all you can do is be there for her.

123
00:07:55,159 --> 00:07:57,500
Just do what you can. Get it?

124
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:01,500
That’s between them. Let them decide.

125
00:08:01,650 --> 00:08:02,500
Trust me.

126
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,000
Let’s talk about you.

127
00:08:07,450 --> 00:08:09,810
You need to pay for your drinks
and the penalty fee.

128
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:11,150
What?

129
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:12,800
I know…

130
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:16,100
what you and Praew did in my bar
the other day.

131
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,300
What did I do?

132
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:26,600
Let’s take pictures.

133
00:08:27,170 --> 00:08:28,400
Sure.

134
00:08:29,940 --> 00:08:31,350
One, two.

135
00:08:33,090 --> 00:08:34,500
Relax, Min.

136
00:08:39,130 --> 00:08:40,299
You look great, Min.

137
00:08:41,100 --> 00:08:41,980
What about me?

138
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:43,650
You look great, too.

139
00:08:43,809 --> 00:08:44,800
But less than her.

140
00:08:46,810 --> 00:08:47,800
Isn’t it obvious?

141
00:08:48,270 --> 00:08:49,920
-I think it’s obvious.
-What is obvious?

142
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:00,870
No matter how tired I am,

143
00:09:00,910 --> 00:09:03,970
I have C Young to keep me young.

144
00:09:05,090 --> 00:09:06,580
Cut. Great.

145
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:07,920
Let’s move on to the next scene.

146
00:09:07,950 --> 00:09:09,980
Please hurry and get changed.

147
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:14,080
Go into the tent and change your outfit.

148
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:15,880
You need to hurry.
The crew is on a tight schedule.

149
00:09:15,940 --> 00:09:18,410
Sure. I’ll do as you want, my stylist.

150
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,250
Shasha.

151
00:09:24,590 --> 00:09:25,900
There are many people outside.

152
00:09:25,980 --> 00:09:27,720
It’s normal for a stylist
to help a model get changed.

153
00:09:27,760 --> 00:09:29,000
No one will suspect it.

154
00:09:30,460 --> 00:09:32,300
Aren’t you going to thank me

155
00:09:32,580 --> 00:09:34,900
for helping you
get a high-paying job like this?

156
00:09:35,860 --> 00:09:36,900
Thank you?

157
00:09:37,190 --> 00:09:39,000
The client chose me
to work on this project.

158
00:09:39,710 --> 00:09:42,700
Don’t you know that I made the request?

159
00:09:42,770 --> 00:09:44,300
I also asked for a raise for you.

160
00:09:45,180 --> 00:09:46,400
I didn’t ask you to do it.

161
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:48,200
You get hooked on me.

162
00:09:53,530 --> 00:09:54,670
I can’t help it.

163
00:10:02,660 --> 00:10:03,500
Shasha.

164
00:10:03,790 --> 00:10:05,300
What are our rules?

165
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:08,400
We are doing it only in a private space.

166
00:10:10,420 --> 00:10:11,400
Be professional.

167
00:10:11,870 --> 00:10:13,300
Separate work from play.

168
00:10:15,580 --> 00:10:16,890
I’m not playing around.

169
00:10:20,670 --> 00:10:21,680
What?

170
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,130
Will you go to a concert with me?

171
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:25,880
No, I don’t like being in the crowd.

172
00:10:25,980 --> 00:10:28,200
Come on. I have no one to go with.

173
00:10:28,930 --> 00:10:29,700
Please.

174
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:32,800
Hurry and get changed.
I’ll think about it.

175
00:10:32,870 --> 00:10:33,700
Sure.

176
00:10:43,580 --> 00:10:45,180
I want to invite you to go up to my room.

177
00:10:45,220 --> 00:10:46,650
But Boom is probably in the room.

178
00:10:47,310 --> 00:10:48,050
It’s okay.

179
00:10:48,090 --> 00:10:49,640
I have something else to do after this.

180
00:10:53,890 --> 00:10:55,450
You can do this when we’re in the car.

181
00:10:55,980 --> 00:10:57,300
But not outside.

182
00:10:57,740 --> 00:10:58,800
I know.

183
00:10:59,090 --> 00:11:01,400
I know where and when I can do it.

184
00:11:06,750 --> 00:11:07,650
Come on.

185
00:11:12,370 --> 00:11:13,900
Your window film is pretty dark.

186
00:11:14,060 --> 00:11:15,100
No one will see us.

187
00:11:16,090 --> 00:11:16,800
Come on.

188
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:22,200
That’s it.

189
00:11:22,980 --> 00:11:23,900
I’m leaving.

190
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:37,650
TEXT ME WHEN YOU GET HOME.

191
00:11:41,380 --> 00:11:42,050
Hey.

192
00:11:42,220 --> 00:11:44,600
So you two are dating?

193
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:47,200
No.

194
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:48,900
But it’s getting close.

195
00:11:49,190 --> 00:11:50,900
She seems to like me a lot.

196
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:54,900
Are you sure you’re not imagining it?

197
00:11:55,250 --> 00:11:57,400
She might see you as a phase.

198
00:11:58,900 --> 00:11:59,980
What makes you think that?

199
00:12:00,910 --> 00:12:03,150
She is a straight woman
who has just gotten out of a relationship.

200
00:12:03,590 --> 00:12:05,510
She might be looking for new challenges.

201
00:12:05,550 --> 00:12:06,810
So she dates a woman.

202
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:08,800
In the end,
she will go back to dating men.

203
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,980
Do you think she will stay with you?

204
00:12:12,380 --> 00:12:13,400
I think

205
00:12:14,610 --> 00:12:15,800
you should…

206
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:18,950
date one of us.

207
00:12:31,450 --> 00:12:32,450
It’s okay.

208
00:12:32,870 --> 00:12:34,100
I like her.

209
00:12:34,620 --> 00:12:35,980
I can’t move on from her.

210
00:12:54,320 --> 00:12:55,200
Hi, hi.

211
00:12:59,380 --> 00:13:01,980
Aren’t you too dressed up
to play badminton?

212
00:13:11,460 --> 00:13:12,200
No.

213
00:13:12,390 --> 00:13:14,090
Every time I go out is
the chance to dress up.

214
00:13:19,140 --> 00:13:21,200
I haven’t played badminton for ages.

215
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:23,980
The last time was
when I played with you in college.

216
00:13:24,260 --> 00:13:25,000
Good.

217
00:13:25,450 --> 00:13:28,200
I take you out to exercise
to boost your endorphins.

218
00:13:28,290 --> 00:13:29,600
So you will feel happy.

219
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:32,300
Just getting back with you,

220
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:35,890
my endorphin level is
already skyrocketing.

221
00:13:37,700 --> 00:13:38,500
You are cute.

222
00:13:38,550 --> 00:13:41,650
Come on. Let’s see if you can beat me.

223
00:13:41,980 --> 00:13:45,300
When I was in high school,
I was a top athlete.

224
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:49,100
Sure.

225
00:13:49,420 --> 00:13:53,200
I’ll show you who the real number one is.

226
00:13:53,670 --> 00:13:54,450
Sure.

227
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:56,900
If I win, will you have a prize for me?

228
00:13:57,390 --> 00:13:58,600
What do you want?

229
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:00,500
I can give you everything.

230
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:02,400
Is that so?

231
00:14:02,790 --> 00:14:03,800
-Is that so?
-Yes.

232
00:14:03,830 --> 00:14:05,300
-Is that so?
-What do you want?

233
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:07,570
Let’s play. Stop joking around.

234
00:14:09,060 --> 00:14:10,060
I’ll beat you.

235
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:10,900
Come on.

236
00:14:45,380 --> 00:14:46,550
I told you.

237
00:14:46,790 --> 00:14:48,400
I, Bambi,

238
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:50,300
never lose to anyone.

239
00:14:50,900 --> 00:14:52,400
I’m going easy on you.

240
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:56,100
Don’t you have sportsmanship, Prim?

241
00:14:56,740 --> 00:14:57,900
Can’t you let me win?

242
00:14:59,060 --> 00:15:00,500
Okay, okay.

243
00:15:01,340 --> 00:15:02,800
I’ll let you win.

244
00:15:04,920 --> 00:15:05,900
What do you want?

245
00:15:10,580 --> 00:15:11,980
Do you want…

246
00:15:12,810 --> 00:15:16,100
an omakase dinner at a rooftop restaurant?

247
00:15:16,590 --> 00:15:20,200
Or a luxurious spa treatment
that matches your lifestyle?

248
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:24,700
Those things, I can buy them myself.

249
00:15:26,730 --> 00:15:27,700
What do you want?

250
00:15:32,260 --> 00:15:33,700
I want…

251
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,980
to sleep over at your place.

252
00:15:40,050 --> 00:15:44,400
I want to spend time with you
like when we were in college.

253
00:15:46,310 --> 00:15:48,230
Stay in the dorm near the campus,

254
00:15:48,270 --> 00:15:51,150
where the owner always overcharged me
for the electricity bill.

255
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:53,200
I never missed it.

256
00:15:55,740 --> 00:15:57,100
Never?

257
00:15:58,870 --> 00:16:01,000
But we had many good memories there.

258
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:06,250
Actually, I missed the time

259
00:16:06,290 --> 00:16:08,700
when we blew out
the birthday candles in the bathtub.

260
00:16:09,610 --> 00:16:10,600
Let’s eat a cake.

261
00:16:14,960 --> 00:16:15,700
Yes.

262
00:16:17,290 --> 00:16:18,700
Can we eat it now?

263
00:16:19,620 --> 00:16:20,600
Why not?

264
00:16:21,290 --> 00:16:22,050
Come on.

265
00:16:23,580 --> 00:16:25,700
I want to eat a cake.

266
00:16:32,470 --> 00:16:33,740
Why are you leaving so soon?

267
00:16:33,780 --> 00:16:35,090
It’s still early in the morning.

268
00:16:35,140 --> 00:16:36,200
I have work to do.

269
00:16:36,390 --> 00:16:38,500
I haven’t prepared outfits
for the shooting tomorrow.

270
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:41,610
We are going to a concert this evening.

271
00:16:41,890 --> 00:16:42,880
You didn’t forget it, right?

272
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:43,800
No.

273
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:44,780
I’m leaving.

274
00:16:44,810 --> 00:16:45,700
Wait.

275
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:47,650
Can I hold you before you go?

276
00:16:52,020 --> 00:16:52,700
That’s enough.

277
00:16:52,740 --> 00:16:53,970
A bit longer.

278
00:16:54,330 --> 00:16:55,970
-Shasha.
-A bit longer.

279
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,200
Shasha.

280
00:17:03,830 --> 00:17:06,079
You have a schedule today.
Did you forget it?

281
00:17:06,220 --> 00:17:08,099
You have a fitting for the fashion week.

282
00:17:08,410 --> 00:17:10,210
If Mac knows that you’re late,
he’ll kill you.

283
00:17:10,300 --> 00:17:11,970
He doesn’t like waiting.

284
00:17:12,119 --> 00:17:13,700
I totally forgot it, Woon.

285
00:17:13,980 --> 00:17:14,770
I’m sorry.

286
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:16,079
I’ve got to go take a shower.

287
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:17,000
I’ll be right back.

288
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,980
Now, you’ve become her regular partner?

289
00:17:28,030 --> 00:17:30,300
It’s not that often.

290
00:17:31,460 --> 00:17:33,400
I’m going to warn you.

291
00:17:34,020 --> 00:17:36,500
I know Shasha well.

292
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:39,400
She will never get serious with you.

293
00:17:40,060 --> 00:17:41,530
She can choose anyone she wants.

294
00:17:43,760 --> 00:17:47,580
All her exes are celebrities and models.

295
00:17:48,170 --> 00:17:49,700
I don’t want you to be too into her.

296
00:17:50,390 --> 00:17:51,300
Thank you.

297
00:17:52,190 --> 00:17:55,000
But I’m not that into her.

298
00:17:55,820 --> 00:17:57,500
I know what I’m doing.

299
00:17:57,940 --> 00:17:59,900
Thank you for your warning,

300
00:18:00,690 --> 00:18:01,980
but it’s unwanted.

301
00:18:08,460 --> 00:18:10,400
Where is Gorya?

302
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:13,120
She left.
She said she didn’t want to wait.

303
00:18:13,530 --> 00:18:16,300
Sha, don’t do this next time.

304
00:18:16,710 --> 00:18:19,800
Don’t hang out with someone
who distracts you from work.

305
00:18:20,940 --> 00:18:22,900
Woon, it has nothing to do with Gorya.

306
00:18:22,970 --> 00:18:23,980
I forgot it.

307
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:27,100
-I’m going to take a shower.
-Hurry up. We’re already late.

308
00:18:31,350 --> 00:18:33,100
I really like your work.

309
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:35,600
Are you also working as a photographer?

310
00:18:35,830 --> 00:18:36,600
Yes.

311
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:38,300
I can take pictures
for all kinds of events.

312
00:18:38,530 --> 00:18:40,510
I hired her
to shoot behind-the-scenes pictures.

313
00:18:40,540 --> 00:18:41,530
She is really good at it.

314
00:18:42,940 --> 00:18:43,680
That’s great.

315
00:18:43,710 --> 00:18:45,200
Can I have your contact info?

316
00:18:45,250 --> 00:18:46,860
I’ll hire you for other work.

317
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:47,850
Sure.

318
00:18:50,580 --> 00:18:51,470
I’ll pay you via QR code scan.

319
00:18:51,910 --> 00:18:54,900
Let’s take a picture
for the photo handover.

320
00:18:59,780 --> 00:19:01,760
One, two, three.

321
00:19:02,350 --> 00:19:03,400
Done.

322
00:19:05,240 --> 00:19:06,610
Thank you so much.

323
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:08,400
If you have work for me,
please feel free to call me.

324
00:19:08,430 --> 00:19:10,200
Sure. I’ll see you.

325
00:19:10,310 --> 00:19:11,850
Sure. Thank you.

326
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:23,700
Thank you, Min.

327
00:19:23,970 --> 00:19:25,460
You don’t need to thank me.

328
00:19:25,510 --> 00:19:27,400
It’s all because of your talents.

329
00:19:27,630 --> 00:19:28,800
I helped you a little.

330
00:19:29,140 --> 00:19:30,500
You got your first sale.

331
00:19:30,730 --> 00:19:31,990
More will follow.

332
00:19:33,350 --> 00:19:34,400
Good.

333
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:37,400
I need money.
I need to get a new apartment.

334
00:19:37,990 --> 00:19:39,850
Why? What happened?

335
00:19:42,130 --> 00:19:44,900
Boom just confessed her feelings for me.

336
00:19:46,330 --> 00:19:47,800
She’s my roommate.

337
00:19:48,780 --> 00:19:51,250
What are you going to do?

338
00:19:52,460 --> 00:19:53,800
I rejected her.

339
00:19:54,170 --> 00:19:57,200
She is someone I trust,
but now she has feelings for me.

340
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:01,880
I get it.

341
00:20:03,050 --> 00:20:04,770
If you don’t feel the same way,

342
00:20:05,660 --> 00:20:07,250
you can’t force it.

343
00:20:08,110 --> 00:20:08,800
Yes.

344
00:20:09,650 --> 00:20:11,200
It’s too bad to lose a friend like this.

345
00:20:11,900 --> 00:20:13,130
We’ve known each other for a long time.

346
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:15,800
You two can still be friends.

347
00:20:16,350 --> 00:20:17,990
You just need to set a boundary.

348
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:19,910
Don’t lead her on…

349
00:20:20,410 --> 00:20:22,200
that you can be more than friends.

350
00:20:24,230 --> 00:20:25,500
You should tell yourself that.

351
00:20:28,380 --> 00:20:29,980
Don’t talk back at me.

352
00:20:32,490 --> 00:20:33,570
I’m just teasing you.

353
00:20:35,590 --> 00:20:37,000
I’ll help you find a condo.

354
00:20:38,250 --> 00:20:41,230
A photographer with potential like you,
you will make a lot of money soon.

355
00:20:41,260 --> 00:20:42,900
Then you can buy your own condo.

356
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:45,600
Let’s go.

357
00:20:46,100 --> 00:20:47,980
Let’s celebrate your first sale.

358
00:20:49,070 --> 00:20:49,800
Yeah.

359
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:06,550
Your ankle is not fully healed.

360
00:21:06,810 --> 00:21:08,490
Why did you ask me
to go work out with you?

361
00:21:08,520 --> 00:21:09,900
Your ankle might hurt again.

362
00:21:10,260 --> 00:21:11,600
It doesn’t hurt.

363
00:21:11,980 --> 00:21:13,300
I just…

364
00:21:14,220 --> 00:21:15,600
want you to take care of me.

365
00:21:17,110 --> 00:21:18,500
So you are pretending?

366
00:21:19,490 --> 00:21:21,900
If I knew getting back together
would be this good,

367
00:21:21,930 --> 00:21:23,730
I would have done it a long time ago.

368
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:26,600
You are willing to get hurt
to have me back?

369
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:29,300
For you, I can do more than that.

370
00:21:31,410 --> 00:21:32,900
You don’t need to do anything.

371
00:21:33,100 --> 00:21:34,900
I’ll take care of you anyway.

372
00:21:36,140 --> 00:21:37,100
Look.

373
00:21:37,540 --> 00:21:41,500
If I came back too late,
I would regret it for the rest of my life.

374
00:21:44,860 --> 00:21:47,240
You are so adorable.

375
00:21:56,750 --> 00:21:58,300
Hi. Min.

376
00:22:00,310 --> 00:22:01,250
Hello, Bambi.

377
00:22:06,080 --> 00:22:08,900
I should go.

378
00:22:09,520 --> 00:22:10,800
I’ll give you a ride.

379
00:22:10,830 --> 00:22:11,700
It’s okay.

380
00:22:12,450 --> 00:22:13,700
I already called my ride.

381
00:22:22,530 --> 00:22:23,300
Bye, Min.

382
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:24,700
Bye.

383
00:22:28,770 --> 00:22:30,660
You’re taking such great care
of the chick.

384
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:34,700
If the chick grows up and bites you,
I’ll laugh at you.

385
00:22:35,650 --> 00:22:37,500
Bambi’s leg hurts.

386
00:22:37,750 --> 00:22:39,700
I just take care of her. That’s all.

387
00:22:42,720 --> 00:22:43,760
Are you free this evening?

388
00:22:43,790 --> 00:22:44,900
Let’s go see a concert.

389
00:22:45,420 --> 00:22:46,880
A client hired us to shoot a music video.

390
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:48,400
She gave me concert tickets.

391
00:22:49,060 --> 00:22:49,800
Sure.

392
00:22:50,510 --> 00:22:51,200
Hey.

393
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:54,530
Can I get another ticket for Bambi?

394
00:22:56,370 --> 00:22:57,100
Sure.

395
00:22:57,320 --> 00:22:58,560
What?

396
00:22:58,580 --> 00:22:59,980
Why do you keep teasing me about this?

397
00:23:00,010 --> 00:23:02,400
I never teased you about Praew.

398
00:23:03,310 --> 00:23:06,530
A lesbian newbie like you
should be careful.

399
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:08,100
Be careful of what?

400
00:23:10,830 --> 00:23:14,500
A pretty girl changing to a lesbian
is rare.

401
00:23:14,750 --> 00:23:16,300
She seems to be really into you.

402
00:23:16,530 --> 00:23:19,010
I don’t think
she wants to be just your experiment.

403
00:23:20,850 --> 00:23:22,100
I don’t mind it.

404
00:23:22,250 --> 00:23:23,700
I like her too.

405
00:23:24,260 --> 00:23:26,100
But I have my own process.

406
00:23:31,740 --> 00:23:33,670
A straight girl like you

407
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:36,040
enjoys playing
with the hearts of lesbians.

408
00:23:49,640 --> 00:23:50,550
Thank you.

409
00:23:52,020 --> 00:23:52,700
Sure.

410
00:23:54,580 --> 00:23:55,980
Wait a sec. Gorya.

411
00:23:56,710 --> 00:23:57,800
Where are you going?

412
00:23:59,420 --> 00:24:00,930
You keep me waiting for too long.

413
00:24:01,090 --> 00:24:02,770
I thought this was your fan meeting.

414
00:24:03,740 --> 00:24:07,650
If you want to date me,
you need to get used to it.

415
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:08,700
Who wants to date you?

416
00:24:09,830 --> 00:24:11,400
I’m sorry, but I don’t understand you.

417
00:24:11,660 --> 00:24:13,020
I’ve never experienced anything like this.

418
00:24:13,060 --> 00:24:14,600
I’m not in the same league as you.

419
00:24:15,770 --> 00:24:16,460
What’s going on?

420
00:24:16,490 --> 00:24:17,390
Shasha.

421
00:24:19,850 --> 00:24:22,400
Wow, Gorya.

422
00:24:26,250 --> 00:24:27,100
Hello, Gorya.

423
00:24:29,180 --> 00:24:30,200
Hey, Bambi.

424
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:32,900
I can’t believe
that you came to this concert.

425
00:24:34,240 --> 00:24:35,650
I’m here to do research for a music video.

426
00:24:36,360 --> 00:24:37,300
I…

427
00:24:38,170 --> 00:24:41,040
I tagged along
as the director’s girlfriend.

428
00:24:44,280 --> 00:24:46,200
When did you two become close?

429
00:24:46,360 --> 00:24:48,300
I thought you kept it strictly business.

430
00:24:48,660 --> 00:24:50,300
You attend the concert together
like you are a couple.

431
00:24:52,490 --> 00:24:53,500
A couple?

432
00:24:53,980 --> 00:24:55,100
We are just friends.

433
00:24:56,670 --> 00:24:58,610
But you two look good together.

434
00:25:00,620 --> 00:25:02,200
No need to set me up with someone.

435
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:04,740
I can find my own girlfriend.

436
00:25:08,790 --> 00:25:09,600
Gorya.

437
00:25:18,740 --> 00:25:20,100
I’ll have one champagne.

438
00:25:25,420 --> 00:25:26,300
Hello.

439
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:28,900
Yes?

440
00:25:29,810 --> 00:25:32,100
Are you Krystal’s fan?

441
00:25:33,380 --> 00:25:35,060
Yes, her songs are beautiful.

442
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:37,600
I’m looking forward to her new album.

443
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:42,100
Do you mind if we chat for a bit?

444
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:45,160
I think you are cute.

445
00:25:46,870 --> 00:25:48,200
No, thank you.

446
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:52,500
But I really want to get to know you.

447
00:25:52,980 --> 00:25:55,480
I want to find someone
who shares similar interests.

448
00:25:57,690 --> 00:26:00,300
I’m sorry. I have a girlfriend.

449
00:26:00,330 --> 00:26:01,700
I’m waiting for her.

450
00:26:01,930 --> 00:26:02,840
Min.

451
00:26:04,960 --> 00:26:05,930
That’s my girlfriend.

452
00:26:10,220 --> 00:26:11,200
Is she really your girlfriend?

453
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:12,910
You two…

454
00:26:13,390 --> 00:26:15,200
look more like sisters.

455
00:26:18,880 --> 00:26:21,600
What do I need to do
to make you believe me?

456
00:26:25,810 --> 00:26:27,300
Do you believe me now?

457
00:26:29,120 --> 00:26:29,900
Okay.

458
00:26:30,390 --> 00:26:31,300
I believe you.

459
00:26:36,240 --> 00:26:37,300
Here is your champagne.

460
00:26:38,670 --> 00:26:39,500
Min.

461
00:26:39,960 --> 00:26:41,200
Aren’t you going to explain to me?

462
00:26:41,530 --> 00:26:44,500
You suddenly kissed my cheek
and said I was your girlfriend.

463
00:26:44,650 --> 00:26:45,800
I will take it seriously.

464
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:47,400
Hold it right there.

465
00:26:47,510 --> 00:26:48,940
She made a move on me,
but I don’t want it.

466
00:26:48,970 --> 00:26:50,100
Can’t you help me?

467
00:26:52,020 --> 00:26:53,400
Then date me for real.

468
00:26:53,780 --> 00:26:55,100
So you won’t need to lie.

469
00:26:55,250 --> 00:26:56,800
Don’t take advantage of the situation.

470
00:26:57,560 --> 00:26:59,400
I didn’t take advantage.

471
00:26:59,800 --> 00:27:01,980
This could hurt my reputation.

472
00:27:02,330 --> 00:27:03,600
You need to take responsibility for it.

473
00:27:04,560 --> 00:27:05,500
What do you want?

474
00:27:08,030 --> 00:27:09,160
Kiss my other cheek.

475
00:27:10,800 --> 00:27:11,900
Not here.

476
00:27:13,850 --> 00:27:14,620
Fine.

477
00:27:15,100 --> 00:27:16,500
I’ll take a rain check.

478
00:27:20,090 --> 00:27:21,400
Can I order a drink?

479
00:27:28,950 --> 00:27:30,100
Let’s go see Prim.

480
00:27:30,560 --> 00:27:31,700
She should have arrived.

481
00:27:59,390 --> 00:28:00,110
Here.

482
00:28:00,480 --> 00:28:01,900
We should call a truce.

483
00:28:02,320 --> 00:28:04,500
Since we now have different targets.

484
00:28:08,240 --> 00:28:09,900
I don’t have a target.

485
00:28:10,080 --> 00:28:11,900
I never pick a fight with anyone.

486
00:28:11,940 --> 00:28:13,100
You are the one

487
00:28:13,540 --> 00:28:14,850
who keeps provoking me.

488
00:28:14,890 --> 00:28:16,400
What?!

489
00:28:16,870 --> 00:28:18,900
Do you still want Prim?

490
00:28:19,330 --> 00:28:21,450
Don’t you get that
she sees you only as a sister?

491
00:28:23,060 --> 00:28:23,900
I get it.

492
00:28:24,170 --> 00:28:25,600
You don’t need to remind me.

493
00:28:29,060 --> 00:28:31,600
You keep messing with me like this.

494
00:28:32,180 --> 00:28:35,490
Is it because you feel insecure
that Prim might be swayed?

495
00:28:36,940 --> 00:28:38,100
I’m not messing with you.

496
00:28:39,050 --> 00:28:40,300
I just want to be your friend.

497
00:28:42,920 --> 00:28:43,980
I like you.

498
00:28:44,210 --> 00:28:45,400
You are quite a fighter.

499
00:28:47,720 --> 00:28:48,800
A fighter?

500
00:28:50,340 --> 00:28:51,600
If I were a fighter,

501
00:28:52,210 --> 00:28:53,610
I would have hit you a long time ago.

502
00:29:01,510 --> 00:29:02,800
Why don’t we give it a try?

503
00:29:08,640 --> 00:29:09,700
Just kidding.

504
00:29:12,600 --> 00:29:14,120
You and Shasha seem like a good match.

505
00:29:14,380 --> 00:29:15,200
It’s not your business.

506
00:29:16,940 --> 00:29:18,400
I don’t want to pry into your business.

507
00:29:18,850 --> 00:29:20,300
I just want to warn you.

508
00:29:20,720 --> 00:29:23,300
Shasha was the same type of person as me.

509
00:29:23,730 --> 00:29:24,900
We like to play games.

510
00:29:26,040 --> 00:29:27,800
When the prey plays hard to get,

511
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:29,800
we just play along.

512
00:29:30,550 --> 00:29:33,300
When the prey falls for us,
we will pull away…

513
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:35,800
and ditch her.

514
00:29:38,790 --> 00:29:40,800
Think of it as advice from a good friend.

515
00:29:54,670 --> 00:29:55,260
Hey.

516
00:29:55,620 --> 00:29:57,250
What’s going on with Shasha and Gorya?

517
00:29:57,650 --> 00:29:58,730
As you see.

518
00:29:58,840 --> 00:29:59,800
That’s wicked.

519
00:30:00,270 --> 00:30:02,100
She keeps it lowkey.

520
00:30:02,770 --> 00:30:05,100
Unlike us, we made it public.

521
00:30:06,020 --> 00:30:07,700
You also keep it lowkey.

522
00:30:08,950 --> 00:30:10,430
Why don’t they go public like us?

523
00:30:10,460 --> 00:30:11,980
-Bambie.
-What?

524
00:30:16,160 --> 00:30:17,500
You look cute today.

525
00:30:21,230 --> 00:30:22,470
You ask me out on a date.

526
00:30:22,970 --> 00:30:24,700
So I need to dress up.

527
00:30:25,150 --> 00:30:26,700
This is not a date.

528
00:30:27,010 --> 00:30:28,200
I came here for work.

529
00:30:28,420 --> 00:30:29,700
So I let you tag along.

530
00:30:30,840 --> 00:30:31,980
Work?

531
00:30:32,510 --> 00:30:34,400
Look around you.

532
00:30:34,970 --> 00:30:36,300
They are here for a date.

533
00:30:36,340 --> 00:30:37,900
Prim and Bambi.

534
00:30:38,420 --> 00:30:39,150
Over there.

535
00:30:39,180 --> 00:30:41,980
Gorya and Shasha.
I’m sure they are on a date.

536
00:30:42,600 --> 00:30:43,800
Except us.

537
00:30:46,090 --> 00:30:47,700
You are imagining things.

538
00:30:48,420 --> 00:30:49,970
You called me your girlfriend.

539
00:30:50,030 --> 00:30:51,700
Then you’ll be my girlfriend for tonight.

540
00:30:58,700 --> 00:30:59,980
Do you want to stand with her?

541
00:31:01,060 --> 00:31:02,200
No, it’s annoying.

542
00:31:13,830 --> 00:31:15,100
Hello, everyone.

543
00:31:15,460 --> 00:31:19,050
Thank you for attending the event
of my new album release, The Dreamer.

544
00:31:19,540 --> 00:31:23,100
I saw many familiar faces today.

545
00:31:23,590 --> 00:31:28,500
I’ll open the show with the song
that made me become widely known.

546
00:31:28,640 --> 00:31:32,500
This song means a lot to me
and someone special.

547
00:31:33,860 --> 00:31:35,980
It’s one of the songs
that I dearly cherish.

548
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:55,980
♪ Can you feel it like I do? ♪

549
00:31:56,250 --> 00:31:59,400
♪ Every moment passing through ♪

550
00:31:59,680 --> 00:32:05,450
♪ For me, it’s all dedicated to you ♪

551
00:32:06,730 --> 00:32:09,800
♪ Since the day we met ♪

552
00:32:10,170 --> 00:32:15,400
♪ You showed me what longing was ♪

553
00:32:16,680 --> 00:32:21,000
♪ Now I know
what love is ‘cause I have you ♪

554
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:24,200
♪ And it isn’t just fate ♪

555
00:32:24,300 --> 00:32:29,600
♪ No one else could ever take your place ♪

556
00:32:30,170 --> 00:32:33,700
♪ It’s only you ♪

557
00:32:33,940 --> 00:32:36,450
♪ You’re more than the word “love” ♪

558
00:32:36,480 --> 00:32:39,980
♪ What you are to me, my love ♪

559
00:32:40,180 --> 00:32:45,200
♪ Just a glance, just a touch ♪

560
00:32:45,390 --> 00:32:48,700
♪ This love will always belong to us ♪

561
00:32:48,860 --> 00:32:53,800
♪ My love,
every time I hear the word “love” ♪

562
00:32:53,900 --> 00:32:56,930
♪ You’re the only one I’m thinking of ♪

563
00:32:58,380 --> 00:32:59,730
♪ I just want you to know ♪

564
00:32:59,760 --> 00:33:03,980
♪ These arms are yours forevermore,
my love ♪

565
00:33:15,700 --> 00:33:17,160
♪ I just want you to know ♪

566
00:33:17,210 --> 00:33:22,600
♪ These arms are yours forevermore,
my love ♪

567
00:34:10,570 --> 00:34:12,100
The music here is nice.

568
00:34:13,429 --> 00:34:14,800
It sounds so in love.

569
00:34:15,590 --> 00:34:16,400
How is it?

570
00:34:16,760 --> 00:34:17,980
Did you get ideas for the music video?

571
00:34:19,400 --> 00:34:20,350
Yes.

572
00:34:21,300 --> 00:34:22,600
I want to make a GL music video.

573
00:34:22,980 --> 00:34:25,100
Music video with two female leads,
I have never done it before.

574
00:34:27,060 --> 00:34:28,929
You pick up an idea
from what you are familiar with.

575
00:34:28,949 --> 00:34:30,800
I know you can do it well.

576
00:34:31,060 --> 00:34:32,330
My girlfriend is talented.

577
00:34:33,520 --> 00:34:35,300
You are complimenting me too much.

578
00:34:35,570 --> 00:34:37,810
You don’t need to believe in me that much.

579
00:34:38,139 --> 00:34:41,100
If I don’t compliment you,
who else would I compliment?

580
00:34:45,670 --> 00:34:47,199
Someone takes pictures of us again.

581
00:34:52,340 --> 00:34:53,400
You need to get used to it.

582
00:34:53,590 --> 00:34:54,969
I’m telling you.

583
00:34:55,400 --> 00:34:58,400
You and Shasha are popular.

584
00:34:59,570 --> 00:35:01,000
You are the type that women like.

585
00:35:02,430 --> 00:35:03,150
Me?

586
00:35:03,360 --> 00:35:04,100
Yes.

587
00:35:05,850 --> 00:35:08,300
Can you stop comparing me to Shasha?

588
00:35:09,270 --> 00:35:11,100
I’m just an aspiring director.

589
00:35:11,700 --> 00:35:14,900
She is an international model.
I’m not in the same league as her.

590
00:35:15,310 --> 00:35:16,100
Why?

591
00:35:16,520 --> 00:35:18,200
You two are very similar.

592
00:35:18,520 --> 00:35:21,100
You are pretty, talented, and confident.

593
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:23,640
I think you two can be friends.

594
00:35:23,680 --> 00:35:25,200
Stop pushing.

595
00:35:25,390 --> 00:35:26,550
I have enough friends.

596
00:35:26,880 --> 00:35:27,950
What’s going on with you?

597
00:35:27,980 --> 00:35:29,900
Why do you want me to be her friend badly?

598
00:35:31,150 --> 00:35:32,800
I just want everyone to get along.

599
00:35:33,670 --> 00:35:35,100
Please practice what you preach.

600
00:35:35,710 --> 00:35:37,450
Can you be nice to Gorya?

601
00:35:39,210 --> 00:35:40,700
She’s like a sister to me.

602
00:35:41,220 --> 00:35:42,380
Stop feeling jealous.

603
00:35:42,420 --> 00:35:44,150
No matter who makes a move on me,
I won’t be interested.

604
00:35:44,990 --> 00:35:46,700
When was I not nice to her?

605
00:35:46,890 --> 00:35:48,500
-I can’t remember it.
-All the time.

606
00:35:48,610 --> 00:35:49,360
-Really?
-Yes.

607
00:35:49,380 --> 00:35:50,240
I don’t know.

608
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:51,600
I’ll keep an eye on you.

609
00:35:51,640 --> 00:35:53,100
Make sure she is just like a sister.

610
00:35:53,440 --> 00:35:56,500
If she calls you with a sweet voice.

611
00:35:57,160 --> 00:35:59,400
Prim, what do you think about that dress?

612
00:35:59,680 --> 00:36:01,920
What do you think about this dress?

613
00:36:02,610 --> 00:36:03,980
Don’t let me catch you doing that.

614
00:36:17,760 --> 00:36:19,500
I’m going to congratulate Kris.

615
00:36:19,680 --> 00:36:20,800
Why don’t you come with me?

616
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:22,900
No. I don’t know her.

617
00:36:23,110 --> 00:36:24,600
Then you should get to know her.

618
00:36:24,670 --> 00:36:25,800
She is popular right now.

619
00:36:25,880 --> 00:36:27,400
You may get a new job from her.

620
00:36:30,230 --> 00:36:30,900
Kris.

621
00:36:33,420 --> 00:36:34,250
Sha.

622
00:36:37,400 --> 00:36:38,600
I thought you wouldn’t come.

623
00:36:38,760 --> 00:36:40,900
Congratulations. Your new song is amazing.

624
00:36:41,150 --> 00:36:41,900
Thank you.

625
00:36:42,910 --> 00:36:45,040
I’m the muse for your first album.

626
00:36:45,080 --> 00:36:45,980
Of course, I have to come.

627
00:36:46,680 --> 00:36:49,600
Who is the inspiration
for your second album?

628
00:36:50,240 --> 00:36:51,200
No one.

629
00:36:51,570 --> 00:36:52,700
I’m single.

630
00:36:53,370 --> 00:36:55,650
It’s more fun to write a song
from someone else’s story.

631
00:36:55,750 --> 00:36:56,700
Sha.

632
00:36:57,160 --> 00:36:57,980
Are you single?

633
00:36:58,120 --> 00:37:00,800
Do you have any fun stories
for me to write a song about?

634
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:04,100
What is going on between you and her?

635
00:37:06,180 --> 00:37:07,400
Is she your new girlfriend?

636
00:37:07,570 --> 00:37:08,570
No.

637
00:37:11,640 --> 00:37:13,700
Kris, this is Gorya.

638
00:37:14,900 --> 00:37:15,900
My stylist.

639
00:37:17,290 --> 00:37:18,910
I thought she was your new girlfriend.

640
00:37:19,340 --> 00:37:20,780
You are cute.

641
00:37:24,720 --> 00:37:30,330
I really want to know
who will be your next girlfriend after me.

642
00:37:32,240 --> 00:37:33,300
That will be hard.

643
00:37:33,570 --> 00:37:35,300
You set the bar high.

644
00:37:35,660 --> 00:37:36,730
Who can compete with you?

645
00:37:36,890 --> 00:37:38,450
It’s not easy to be my girlfriend.

646
00:37:38,620 --> 00:37:39,500
That’s true.

647
00:37:40,590 --> 00:37:41,970
You are picky.

648
00:37:42,860 --> 00:37:43,800
A little.

649
00:37:44,210 --> 00:37:46,300
Are you still living in the same place?

650
00:37:46,700 --> 00:37:48,700
Of course. Where else can I move to?

651
00:37:49,960 --> 00:37:51,300
I’ll visit you when I have free time.

652
00:37:52,740 --> 00:37:53,600
Sure.

653
00:37:54,340 --> 00:37:56,400
Shasha, I’m leaving.

654
00:37:58,000 --> 00:37:59,600
Congratulations, Krystal.

655
00:37:59,750 --> 00:38:00,900
Your new song is amazing.

656
00:38:01,450 --> 00:38:03,300
Are you going to party with us?

657
00:38:03,760 --> 00:38:05,100
I want to get to know you.

658
00:38:06,110 --> 00:38:08,150
We may have a chance
to work together in the future.

659
00:38:09,070 --> 00:38:10,300
Maybe next time.

660
00:38:10,560 --> 00:38:12,090
I have to work tomorrow.

661
00:38:13,170 --> 00:38:14,150
That’s too bad.

662
00:38:14,650 --> 00:38:15,410
It’s okay.

663
00:38:20,460 --> 00:38:21,400
I’ll be right back.

664
00:38:28,220 --> 00:38:29,000
Gorya.

665
00:38:32,700 --> 00:38:33,770
Gorya, where are you going?

666
00:38:33,810 --> 00:38:34,500
Gorya.

667
00:38:36,930 --> 00:38:37,980
I’m going home to rest.

668
00:38:39,090 --> 00:38:39,900
Okay.

669
00:38:40,990 --> 00:38:42,500
Are you jealous because of Kris?

670
00:38:44,630 --> 00:38:45,900
Aren’t you a bit full of yourself?

671
00:38:46,510 --> 00:38:47,250
Then what?

672
00:38:47,290 --> 00:38:49,480
Did Woonsen say something to you?

673
00:38:49,620 --> 00:38:51,200
No one said anything to me.

674
00:38:51,500 --> 00:38:52,400
I’m just tired.

675
00:38:52,930 --> 00:38:53,900
I want to rest.

676
00:38:54,160 --> 00:38:55,400
Then go to my condo and rest.

677
00:38:55,730 --> 00:38:56,470
No.

678
00:38:57,320 --> 00:38:58,400
Why do I need to go there often?

679
00:38:58,590 --> 00:39:00,900
You should go back
and enjoy the night with her.

680
00:39:03,370 --> 00:39:04,100
Okay.

681
00:39:05,070 --> 00:39:06,900
There’s nothing between Kris and me.

682
00:39:07,710 --> 00:39:09,200
You are someone special to me.

683
00:39:10,620 --> 00:39:11,800
You are my only one.

684
00:39:12,200 --> 00:39:13,000
Thank you.

685
00:39:13,520 --> 00:39:15,400
But you don’t need to give me any title.

686
00:39:16,140 --> 00:39:17,500
We are not that compatible.

687
00:39:17,840 --> 00:39:20,700
Our friend with benefits deal.
Let’s call it off.

688
00:39:20,960 --> 00:39:21,800
I’m done.

689
00:39:23,050 --> 00:39:26,400
You came to my door and made the offer.

690
00:39:26,560 --> 00:39:27,980
I didn’t force you to do it.

691
00:39:28,350 --> 00:39:29,980
Yes, I was wrong.

692
00:39:31,190 --> 00:39:32,470
Now, I’ve come to my senses.

693
00:39:32,520 --> 00:39:33,500
Happy?

694
00:39:34,900 --> 00:39:35,980
Let’s go back to my condo and talk.

695
00:39:36,060 --> 00:39:36,900
No.

696
00:39:37,160 --> 00:39:37,980
I have my own home.

697
00:39:38,590 --> 00:39:39,780
I’m going home to rest.

698
00:39:56,230 --> 00:39:57,230
What is wrong with you?

699
00:39:59,040 --> 00:40:00,770
I just want you to come home with me.

700
00:40:04,050 --> 00:40:05,200
Don’t do this again.

701
00:40:06,180 --> 00:40:07,600
Otherwise, my anger…

702
00:40:08,330 --> 00:40:09,500
will turn into hatred.

703
00:40:44,540 --> 00:40:45,980
I’m sorry for keeping you waiting.

704
00:40:46,010 --> 00:40:47,200
I was talking to my client.

705
00:40:47,750 --> 00:40:48,600
It’s okay.

706
00:40:48,790 --> 00:40:50,150
You can take as much time as you want.

707
00:40:50,190 --> 00:40:51,360
I’ll wait for you.

708
00:40:52,290 --> 00:40:53,600
Come on. Let’s go home.

709
00:40:53,640 --> 00:40:54,900
I’ll give you a ride home.

710
00:40:55,460 --> 00:40:56,300
No.

711
00:40:56,500 --> 00:40:57,900
I don’t want to go home yet.

712
00:40:58,310 --> 00:40:59,410
I don’t want this date to end yet.

713
00:41:00,900 --> 00:41:03,100
You’re trying hard to insist
that this is a date.

714
00:41:09,210 --> 00:41:10,300
Fine, it’s a date.

715
00:41:17,790 --> 00:41:18,650
Let’s go.

716
00:41:26,340 --> 00:41:27,100
Ouch.

717
00:41:27,940 --> 00:41:29,300
You bumped into my head.

718
00:41:30,200 --> 00:41:30,960
Bambi.

719
00:41:30,990 --> 00:41:32,530
What?

720
00:41:32,560 --> 00:41:34,100
-Sit here.
-Where?

721
00:41:36,360 --> 00:41:38,700
Hey, I’m not that drunk.

722
00:41:38,900 --> 00:41:42,800
Then why did you let me carry you?
You are heavy.

723
00:41:43,110 --> 00:41:43,980
Heavy?

724
00:41:44,090 --> 00:41:45,400
I’m petite.

725
00:41:45,460 --> 00:41:47,300
I’m easy to carry like a miniature.

726
00:41:48,800 --> 00:41:49,500
Hey.

727
00:41:50,110 --> 00:41:51,300
Where are you going?

728
00:41:52,710 --> 00:41:53,600
Hold me.

729
00:41:54,300 --> 00:41:57,800
I’ll go get water and aspirin
for your hangover in the morning.

730
00:41:58,390 --> 00:41:59,800
Don’t go.

731
00:41:59,870 --> 00:42:01,700
I’m drunk on nothing.

732
00:42:03,010 --> 00:42:04,200
I’m drunk on you.

733
00:42:04,690 --> 00:42:06,600
I pretend to be drunk for your attention.

734
00:42:07,340 --> 00:42:10,800
Prim, Prim, Prim.

735
00:42:13,240 --> 00:42:14,310
I noticed it.

736
00:42:14,540 --> 00:42:16,420
You barely drank.

737
00:42:16,650 --> 00:42:18,800
Because you want to take care of me.

738
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:20,720
Just like when we were in college.

739
00:42:20,740 --> 00:42:23,000
When we went to a nightclub,
you only had two drinks.

740
00:42:23,090 --> 00:42:26,100
You kept an eye on me
so I wouldn’t go up and dance on stage.

741
00:42:27,760 --> 00:42:29,980
When I tried to stop you,
have you ever listened to me?

742
00:42:30,770 --> 00:42:32,650
Before I could take you down,

743
00:42:32,700 --> 00:42:35,800
you had already become a star
of the nightclub near our campus.

744
00:42:36,950 --> 00:42:38,410
We had a great time back then.

745
00:42:40,400 --> 00:42:41,980
But I’m going to make today…

746
00:42:43,980 --> 00:42:45,500
even better.

747
00:42:48,780 --> 00:42:49,600
Good.

748
00:42:50,380 --> 00:42:51,800
Stop talking about the past.

749
00:42:54,250 --> 00:42:55,800
Back then,

750
00:42:56,530 --> 00:42:58,900
I was too focused on the work
that I forgot about you.

751
00:42:59,640 --> 00:43:02,840
Now, I can balance my priorities.
I’m a new person.

752
00:43:05,740 --> 00:43:07,500
You don’t need to choose me over work.

753
00:43:08,820 --> 00:43:10,600
Now, I get it.

754
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:13,100
Work is important to you.

755
00:43:13,550 --> 00:43:15,470
I was unreasonable back then.

756
00:43:15,500 --> 00:43:17,000
I wanted things to go my way.

757
00:43:20,280 --> 00:43:21,100
That’s enough.

758
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,100
Stop talking about the past.

759
00:43:24,420 --> 00:43:26,100
Let’s focus on the present.

760
00:43:31,250 --> 00:43:33,000
My future.

761
00:43:34,180 --> 00:43:35,500
If you are not a part of it,

762
00:43:36,730 --> 00:43:38,500
I will never be happy.

763
00:43:41,760 --> 00:43:44,300
I want you to be by my side when I fall

764
00:43:45,710 --> 00:43:47,500
and when I win an award.

765
00:43:49,020 --> 00:43:49,900
But…

766
00:43:51,820 --> 00:43:53,600
You’ve won an award.

767
00:44:06,180 --> 00:44:10,700
My all-time favorite girlfriend award.

768
00:45:42,780 --> 00:45:44,700
I don’t expect anything from you.

769
00:45:44,820 --> 00:45:47,090
If you are happy when you take care of me,

770
00:45:47,120 --> 00:45:48,210
then you should do it.

771
00:45:48,420 --> 00:45:51,500
You need to stop being nosy
and mind your own business.

772
00:45:51,570 --> 00:45:53,650
You got played by your manager
and don’t even realize it.

773
00:45:53,820 --> 00:45:54,700
What do you mean?

774
00:45:57,540 --> 00:46:00,400
After you broke up with me,
are you really dating a woman?

775
00:46:00,460 --> 00:46:02,200
-Being a lesbian is more exciting?
-Praew.

776
00:46:04,540 --> 00:46:05,980
We are closed.

777
00:46:06,350 --> 00:46:07,550
Can you hold me?

778
00:46:08,290 --> 00:46:11,600
I just want to feel that I am wanted.

779
00:46:13,860 --> 00:46:15,000
I will only hold you.
